What I'd like to discuss here is all about uniform concepts I've learnt since. And I wanna summarize them.
About uniform continuity In calculus, there exists a concept called Continuity as expressed below: f(x) is continuous at x0⇔∀ϵ∈ℝ∃δ∈ℝ:|x−x0|&lt;δ⇒|f(x)−f(x0)|&lt;ϵ\begin{aligned}&amp;\text{$f(x)$ is continuous at $x_0$}\Leftrightarrow\\ &amp;\forall{\epsilon\in \mathbb R}\exists{\delta\in \mathbb R} : |x-x_0|&lt;\delta \Rightarrow |f(x)-f(x_0)|&lt;\epsilon\end{aligned} As is seen above, δ\delta is somewhere dependent towards x0x_0. What if we genernalize that idea such that δ\delta shall be dependent not to x0x_0 but to an interval?
